HEADWORD: Azimuthal
<hw>Az"i*muth`al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to the azimuth; in a horizontal circle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Azimuthal error</b></col> <cd>of a transit instrument,
its deviation in azimuth from the plane of the meridian.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

